--- /dev/null
+++ b/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md
@@ -0,0 +1,192 @@
+# False Positive Report — CVE-2026-42039 (axios 0.21.4)
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| **CVE** | CVE-2026-42039 |
+| **Advisory** | [GHSA-62hf-57xw-28j9](https://github.com/axios/axios/security/advisories/GHSA-62hf-57xw-28j9) |
+| **Component** | axios |
+| **Version in use** | 0.21.4 |
+| **Weakness** | CWE-674 — Uncontrolled Recursion |
+| **CVSS** | 7.5 (HIGH, CVSS 3.1) / 6.9 (MEDIUM, CVSS 4.0) |
+| **Declared affected range** | `< 0.31.1` and `1.0.0 – 1.15.0` |
+| **Determination for 0.21.4** | ❌ **NOT AFFECTED — False Positive** |
+| **VEX status / justification** | `not_affected` / `vulnerable_code_not_present` |
+| **Assessed on** | 2026-05-29 |
+
+---
+
+## 1. What the vulnerability actually is
+
+CVE-2026-42039 is an **uncontrolled-recursion** flaw in axios's **`toFormData` helper**
+(`lib/helpers/toFormData.js`). That helper recursively walks a nested
+plain-object/array request body to serialize it into a `FormData` instance. It
+applies **no recursion-depth limit and no visited-node tracking**, so a
+sufficiently deep (or self-referential) input object drives the call stack past
+its limit and throws a `RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded`,
+crashing the process (denial of service).
+
+The vulnerable path is reached when a caller passes a deeply nested object as
+request `data` and axios converts it via `toFormData` (e.g. the
+`formSerializer` / automatic FormData serialization introduced in later
+versions).
+
+---
+
+## 2. Why 0.21.4 is not affected
+
+**The vulnerable function does not exist in this version.**
+
+`toFormData` was introduced into axios **around v0.27.0**. Release **0.21.4
+predates it**, so the recursive serializer the CVE targets was never shipped in
+this codebase. There is no code path — vulnerable or otherwise — that
+recursively converts an object into `FormData`.
+
+### Evidence (verified against this exact tree)
+
+**(a) No `toFormData` symbol anywhere in the library:**
+
+```console
+$ grep -rn "toFormData" lib/ index.js index.d.ts
+# (no matches)
+```
+
+**(b) No `lib/helpers/toFormData.js` file exists:**
+
+```console
+$ ls lib/helpers/
+bind.js              cookies.js            isAbsoluteURL.js     parseHeaders.js
+buildURL.js          deprecatedMethod.js   isAxiosError.js      spread.js
+combineURLs.js       isURLSameOrigin.js    normalizeHeaderName.js  validator.js
+sanitizeHeaderValue.js  shouldBypassProxy.js
+#   ^ no toFormData.js
+```
+
+**(c) Every `FormData` reference in 0.21.4 is non-recursive type-detection or
+pass-through — none of it walks nested objects:**
+
+| Location | What it does | Recurses? |
+|----------|--------------|-----------|
+| [`lib/utils.js:56`](lib/utils.js#L56) | `isFormData(val)` → `val instanceof FormData` (a boolean type check) | No |
+| [`lib/defaults.js:58`](lib/defaults.js#L58) | If `data` **is already** a `FormData`, return it unchanged | No |
+| [`lib/adapters/xhr.js:18`](lib/adapters/xhr.js#L18) | Hands an existing `FormData` straight to `XMLHttpRequest.send()` | No |
+
+In 0.21.4 a `FormData` body is treated as an opaque, already-built object. axios
+never *constructs* a `FormData` from a nested object here, so there is no
+recursive descent to overflow.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Why the scanner still flags it (root cause of the false positive)
+
+Security advisories declare their affected set by **published version range**,
+and GHSA-62hf-57xw-28j9 lists `< 0.31.1`. Version `0.21.4` is numerically inside
+that range, so a **version-only** matcher (the default for most SCA/dependency
+scanners) reports a hit.
+
+However, the affected *code* (`toFormData`) only existed in the subset of 0.x
+releases that shipped it — roughly **0.27.0 through 0.31.0**. The declared range
+`< 0.31.1` is a coarse upper bound that incidentally also covers older releases
+like 0.21.4 that never contained the function.
+
+> **Version range matched, but the vulnerable function is absent.**
+> This is classic version-range over-matching, not a real exposure.
+
+---
+
+## 4. Scope and honesty note
+
+This determination is **specific to CVE-2026-42039**. It means only:
+
+> The function targeted by this CVE is not present in axios 0.21.4, so this
+> particular vulnerability cannot be triggered in this build.
+
+It is **not** a statement that axios 0.21.4 is secure overall. 0.21.4 is an old
+release with multiple other applicable CVEs. In this tree, the following
+*real* and applicable issues have been backported separately:
+
+- **CVE-2025-62718** & **CVE-2026-42043** — `NO_PROXY` bypass / SSRF
+  (see [`SECURITY_BACKPORT.md`](SECURITY_BACKPORT.md))
+- **CVE-2026-42033** — prototype-pollution gadgets in config merge
+
+Upgrading off the 0.x line remains the recommended long-term action.
+
+---
+
+## 5. Suggested suppression entries
+
+Use whichever matches your scanner. Justification in all cases:
+*"vulnerable function `toFormData` not present in axios 0.21.4."*
+
+**OWASP Dependency-Check** (`suppression.xml`):
+
+```xml
+<suppress>
+  <notes><![CDATA[
+    CVE-2026-42039 affects axios's toFormData helper (uncontrolled recursion).
+    toFormData was introduced ~v0.27.0 and does not exist in 0.21.4.
+    Vulnerable code not present -> not affected.
+  ]]></notes>
+  <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:npm/axios@0\.21\.4$</packageUrl>
+  <cve>CVE-2026-42039</cve>
+</suppress>
+```
+
+**npm audit / better-npm-audit** (`.nsprc`):
+
+```json
+{
+  "exceptions": {
+    "CVE-2026-42039": {
+      "active": true,
+      "notes": "axios 0.21.4 has no toFormData helper (added ~0.27.0); vulnerable code not present."
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+**Snyk** (`.snyk`):
+
+```yaml
+version: v1.25.0
+ignore:
+  SNYK-JS-AXIOS-CVE-2026-42039:
+    - '*':
+        reason: >-
+          toFormData helper (the vulnerable function) is absent in axios 0.21.4;
+          introduced ~0.27.0. Vulnerable code not present.
+        expires: 2027-05-29T00:00:00.000Z
+```
+
+**OpenVEX** (statement excerpt):
+
+```json
+{
+  "statements": [
+    {
+      "vulnerability": { "name": "CVE-2026-42039" },
+      "products": [{ "@id": "pkg:npm/axios@0.21.4" }],
+      "status": "not_affected",
+      "justification": "vulnerable_code_not_present",
+      "impact_statement": "The toFormData helper targeted by this CVE was introduced ~v0.27.0 and is not present in axios 0.21.4."
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## 6. Verification commands (reproduce this determination)
+
+```console
+# 1. No toFormData symbol in the shipped library:
+grep -rn "toFormData" lib/ index.js index.d.ts   # expect: no output
+
+# 2. No toFormData helper file:
+ls lib/helpers/ | grep -i toformdata              # expect: no output
+
+# 3. Confirm FormData is only detected/passed through, never built recursively:
+grep -rn "FormData" lib/                          # expect: only isFormData + pass-through
+```
+
+All three commands were run against this tree and confirm the vulnerable
+function is absent.

